e the move.\r\n\r\n<h3>Moving Boxes and Packing Services in Maine & New Hampshire</h3>\r\n\r\nA great move begins with our packers & movers using the proper packing supplies to avoid accidents. At Liberty Bell Moving and Storage, we have only the best boxes for sale. Proper packing material and moving boxes are essential for a  great moving experience.\r\n\r\n<h3>Need Moving Supplies?</h3>\r\n\r\nShould you decide to save  money and pack yourself; Liberty Bell has a wide assortment of moving boxes for sale. We can deliver any type of packing boxes — from dish packing boxes to wardrobe boxes for your garments. And if you have extra moving supplies after your move, we will buy unused boxes back.\r\n\r\n<h3>Crating Services</h3>\r\n\r\nLiberty Bell also provides services for larger, heavier items and such as: \r\n<ul>\r\n<li>pool table crates</li>\r\n<li>grandfather clock crates</li>\r\n<li>granite table top crates</li>\r\n<li>other larger fragile items</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>','Packing Services','','inherit','open','open','','22-revision-3','','','2012-01-11 02:00:07','2012-01-11 02:00:07','',22,'http://libertybellmoving.com/22-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(360,1,'2012-01-11 01:57:30','2012-01-11 01:57:30','<h3 class=\"top\">Moving your Piano is easy with our Piano Movers!</h3>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"hometext\">\r\n<a href=\"http://libertybellmoving.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/12/piano_moving.jpeg\"><img src=\"http://libertybellmoving.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/12/piano_moving.jpeg\" alt=\"\" title=\"long_haul_moves\" width=\"150\" height=\"152\" class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-119\" /></a>From the smallest Spinets to the largest Grand Piano, piano moving performed by Liberty Bell Moving offers homeowners peace of mind knowing their piano is being moved by trained piano movers.\r\n\r\nOur trained and registered Maine piano movers and piano tuners take pride in the careful disassembly padding, strapping, shipping and reassembly of your piano. Contact us today about our Piano Moving Services!\r\n\r\n<h3>Trust Liberty Bell Moving with your Piano Move Today!</h3>\r\n\r\nFrom the smallest Spinets to the largest Grand Piano, piano moving performed by Liberty Bell Moving offers homeowners peace of mind knowing their piano is being moved by trained piano movers.\r\n\r\nOur trained and registered Maine piano movers and piano tuners take pride in the careful disassembly padding, strapping, shipping and reassembly of your piano.\r\n\r\n<h3>Liberty Bell Moving has the experience and equipment to handle:</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>moving spinet pianos</li>\r\n<li>moving console pianos</li>\r\n<li>moving player pianos</li>\r\n<li>moving studio pianos</li>\r\n<li>moving upright pianos</li>\r\n<li>moving baby grand pianos</li>\r\n<li>moving full grand pianos</li>\r\n<li>moving concert grand piano</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nIf you have us move and tune your piano, we recommend that the piano should be acclimated to the home for 3-4 weeks before scheduling a date for a piano tuning by our Registered Piano Technician.\r\n\r\n<h3>Piano Information</h3>\r\n\r\nBesides the fact that piano is heavy – it is also bulky and has an uneven distribution of weight. With that comes inertia and problems with balancing when you try to maneuver it, especially when moving the piano in a narrow passage. Professional piano movers know that the piano is extremely sensitive to a shock because it has a very delicate inner mechanism.\r\n\r\nThe iron frame, also called the “plate”, sits atop the soundboard, and serves as the primary bulwark against the force of string tension (in a modern grand the total string tension can approach 20 tons). The frame is made of cast iron and if it cracks the damage is irreparable.\r\n\r\nNo matter how much care we put into moving your piano, we always recommend having it tuned post move. Pianos are knocked out of tune very easily. If a perfect pitch is a priority, consider having our registered piano tuner bring the original sound back i